tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and mildly low total COâ, suggesting impaired renal function and possible tubular dysfunction. The low HbA1c with normal glucose argues against chronic hyperglycemia. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying renal or urinary tract pathology. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible acute or chronic kidney disease.
